# Project Context ‚Äî C# Test Explorer

VS Code extension (TypeScript) that discovers, runs, and debugs C# tests (NUnit, xUnit, MSTest) via a sidebar tree view.

## Tech Stack
- TypeScript, VS Code Extension API (^1.85.0)
- Build: esbuild, compiled to `out/`
- Activated when workspace contains `*.csproj`

## Architecture

```
src/
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ extension.ts              # Entry point: activates CSharpTestController, registers commands
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ testController.ts         # Core orchestrator: uses VS Code TestController API, wires discovery + execution
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ testTreeProvider.ts       # TreeDataProvider for the sidebar test tree view
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ discovery/
‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ projectDetector.ts    # Finds .csproj files in the workspace
‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ dotnetDiscoverer.ts   # Runs `dotnet test --list-tests` to discover tests
‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ sourceMapper.ts       # Maps discovered tests back to source file locations
‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ patterns.ts           # Shared regex patterns for C# test attribute/class/method detection
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ execution/
‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ testRunner.ts         # Executes `dotnet test` with filters
‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ filterBuilder.ts      # Builds --filter expressions for dotnet test
‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ trxParser.ts          # Parses TRX result files
‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ resultMatcher.ts      # Matches TRX results back to TestItems
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ debug/
‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ debugLauncher.ts      # Launches dotnet test with debugger attached
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ ui/
‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ statusBarManager.ts   # Status bar indicator for test runs
‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ utils/
    ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ outputChannel.ts      # Logging via VS Code OutputChannel
    ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ dotnetCli.ts          # Wrapper for spawning dotnet CLI processes
    ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ testItemUtils.ts      # Shared helpers for TestItem tag storage and parent-chain lookups
```

## Key Flows
1. **Discovery**: projectDetector ‚Üí dotnetDiscoverer ‚Üí sourceMapper ‚Üí testController builds TestItem tree
2. **Execution**: testController ‚Üí filterBuilder ‚Üí testRunner ‚Üí trxParser ‚Üí resultMatcher ‚Üí updates TestItem states
3. **Debug**: testController ‚Üí debugLauncher (attaches VS Code debugger to dotnet test process)

## Commands (registered in extension.ts)
- `csharpTestExplorer.refreshTests` ‚Äî re-discover all tests
- `csharpTestExplorer.runAll` ‚Äî run every discovered test
- `csharpTestExplorer.runTest` ‚Äî run a specific tree node
- `csharpTestExplorer.debugTest` ‚Äî debug a specific tree node
- `csharpTestExplorer.showOutput` ‚Äî open the output channel

## Keeping This Rule Up-to-Date

After completing work on a GitHub issue, check whether the changes require updating this rule. Update it if any of the following occurred:

- **New file or module added** ‚Äî add it to the Architecture tree with a one-line description.
- **File deleted or renamed** ‚Äî update or remove the corresponding entry.
- **New command registered** ‚Äî add it to the Commands section.
- **New key flow introduced or existing flow changed** ‚Äî update the Key Flows section.
- **Tech stack change** (new dependency, framework version bump, build tool change) ‚Äî update Tech Stack.
- **Architectural shift** (new top-level directory, module split/merge) ‚Äî restructure the Architecture tree accordingly.

Do NOT update this rule for:
- Bug fixes that don't change the architecture.
- Internal refactors within a single file (e.g., extracting a private method).
- Test-only changes.

When updating, keep descriptions to one line per file/entry. This rule should stay concise ‚Äî it's a map, not documentation.
